body:
A duplicate of #1654 with additional commits that automatically address incorrect style, created by [Restyled][]. Since the original Pull Request was opened as a fork in a contributor's repository, we are unable to create a Pull Request branching from it with only the style fixes. The following Restylers [made fixes](https://restyled.io/gh/TokTok/repos/c-toxcore/jobs/1366377): - astyle - clang-format To incorporate these changes, you can either: 1. Merge this Pull Request *instead of* the original, or 1. Ask your contributor to locally incorporate these commits and push them to the original Pull Request
Expand for example instructions ```console git remote add upstream https://github.com/TokTok/c-toxcore.git git fetch upstream pull//head git merge --ff-only FETCH_HEAD git push ```
**NOTE**: As work continues on the original Pull Request, this process will re-run and update (force-push) this Pull Request with updated style fixes as necessary. If the style is fixed manually at any point (i.e. this process finds no fixes to make), this Pull Request will be closed automatically. Sorry if this was unexpected. To disable it, see our [documentation][]. [restyled]: https://restyled.io [documentation]: https://github.com/restyled-io/restyled.io/wiki/Disabling-Restyled --- This change isâ€‚[](https://reviewable.io/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/1784)

Add new feature - topic lock

Group founders can now toggle a topic lock. When the lock is enabled

anyone can change the topic

online to offline. This will need to be reverted once we merge with the
mainnet, or when the TCP bug gets fixed

commit.message:
Refactor the way we send packets and remove ugly hack

We now store the plaintext data in the send array and encrypt it on each send attempt.
This prevents us from sending packets from our send array that were encrypted with
an old shared key that the recipient no longer has the means to decrypt. This in
turn allows us to remove the ugly hack where we were keeping he last shared key
around to decrypt recent messages

commit.message:
Add topic checksum to address syncing issues

This makes sure that the entire group will get the same topic if two or more
peers attempt to change the topic at the exact same time. Previously, peers
would just over-ride their current topic if they got a new one with the
same version, leading to some peers potentially seeing a different topic
than other peers without any way to detect it. Now the topic with the
highest checksum wins the race.

commit.message:
Refactor peer ID generation

This accounts for the unlikely but possible scenario where the
base ID would wrap-around back to zero. We also now reserve
UINT32_MAX as an invalid ID to indicate an error for both
internal purposes and the public API.

commit.message:
No longer send chat ID hash in plaintext packet headers

This was used to identify the group that a groupchat packet was intended for
however due to the public nature of DHT groupchats, it would expose the fact
that someone was in a particular group to anyone who looked.

We now use a hash of the recipient's group permanent public key for handshake
packets, and a hash of the recipient's session public key associated
with the sender's connection for all other packets.

This significantly reduces the ability of adversaries from determining that a
target is in a particular group.
